| type    = notice
| image   = [[File:Ambox_notice.png|40px|alt=Info]]
| text    = <u>Update</u>: 
* {{project name}} now ships with a desktop file and menu options which affect the [[#Security Slider|security slider]] setting after first launching Tor Browser. This provides a choice between maximum security (high setting) versus maximum usability (low setting); see [https://forums.whonix.org/t/ship-an-additional-version-of-tor-browser-with-security-slider-settings-to-high-by-default/7591 this forum thread] for further details. 
* Occasionally users report that setting the slider to "Safest" mode still allows JavaScript to operate in "Standard" mode; refer to this [https://forums.whonix.org/t/broken-security-slider/8675 forum thread] for a fix if you are affected. <ref>To fix this problem, close Tor Browser then run: {{CodeSelect|code=
