The [[Manually_Downloading_Tor_Browser|manual Tor Browser download]] procedure assumes essential knowledge of:

* <u>Software Verification</u>: The Tor Browser package must be verified with PGP, using the associated file signature and Tor signing keys (relevant links are provided). <ref>{{project_name}} is not a standalone package, but a complete operating system. {{project_name}} has a small team, while torproject.org has a much larger community and dedicated, paid support staff. Therefore, {{project_name}} users are expected to learn Tor Browser essentials in the first instance.</ref>
* <u>Troubleshooting</u>: If Tor Browser problems occur in {{project_name}} such as webpages failing to resolve, then:
** The same tests should be performed on the host ({{non_q_project_name_short}}) or in a non-{{project_name}} VM ({{q_project_name}}); see [[Install_Tor_Browser_Outside_of_{{project_name_short}}|Non-{{project_name}} Tor Browser]]. This step helps to determine whether the problem is related to {{project_name}} or not. 
