== Tor Browser Consumes 100% CPU after Clock Sync or Suspend/Resume ==

An upstream [https://gitlab.torproject.org/tpo/applications/tor-browser/-/issues/29497 bug] in Tor Browser causes the <code>firefox.real</code> process to consume excessive CPU whenever the connection to Tor's <code>ControlPort</code> is broken, which continues until Tor Browser is restarted. This is known to occur when the [[sdwdate]] clock synchronization daemon is restarted in Whonix-Gateway, whether manually via the [[sdwdate-gui]] time synchronization systray, or automatically via post-resume hooks. For details, refer to the related forum [http://forums.whonix.org/t/bug-restart-of-sdwdate-in-whonix-gateway-causes-100-cpu-use-of-tor-browser-in-whonix-workstation/9541/18 discussion]. ([https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-issues/issues/4969 original report on Qubes issue tracker])

As a workaround:

# Open <code>about:config</code> in the Tor Browser URL bar.
# Search for and set <code>extensions.torbutton.display_circuit</code> to <code>false</code>.
# Restart Tor Browser.

In {{q_project_name}}, see [https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/disposable-customization/ Disposable Customization] to make this change persistent in Disposables.

